// vim: filetype=go
// Shared PColumn spec setup for both the legacy single-PDB body path and
// the per-clonotype PrimaryRef path. Declares axes + column specs for the
// motifs, cysteines, and scores PFrames the Python software produces.
//
// `axesSpec` / `columnSpecs` / `columnIds` mirror the parquet column layout
// `software/src/pframe_writer.py` writes. The per-clonotype path adds a
// leading `pl7.app/vdj/scClonotypeKey` axis via `pframes.processColumn`'s
// input-axis prepending; the legacy single-PDB path uses an explicit
// `structureId` axis on the scores frame.

ll := import("@platforma-sdk/workflow-tengo:ll")

